            ya know. Bayern Munich could hog possession even more than man city if they use Alcantra and Rudy as deep lying playmakers and James Rodriguez as attacking midfielder. Although against Psg this wasn't the case. But it had to do more with tactics than anything else. Oh man, Heynkes never really disappoint. He would always rotate his squad. Making his fringe players fit and the entire squad hungry for competition. I still remember in 2012 cl semifinal where Heynkes outsmarted Jose Mourinho just by resting and rotating his players. Whereas Mourinho obviously didn't his players and that resulted in fresher and more motivated Bayern Munich outlasting Real Madrid in a gruelling semifinal match. I think squad rotation is a risky strategy but nobody does better than Heynkes does it Mia San Mia.
